-- ============================================================
-- Manoel Olímpio de Souza, known as Mestre Índio do Mercado Modelo,
-- is a pioneer who brought capoeira to Rio Grande do Sul in the
-- early 1970s. Born on Ilha de Bom Jesus dos Passos near Salvador,
-- he trained under Mestre Pelé da Bomba and founded Grupo de
-- Capoeira Oxóssi (1968). He developed "Capoeira de Rua" with
-- Angolan foundation and is famous for his "chapa da morte" kick.
--
-- BIRTH YEAR ESTIMATION:
-- Primary source (capoeiradomercado.com) states July 26, 1950,
-- born on Ilha de Bom Jesus dos Passos. Other sources say 1955
-- (likely rounded/approximate). Using 1950 with exact precision
-- as the most detailed source provides complete birth date.
--
-- APELIDO CONTEXT:
-- Uses apelido_context 'Mercado Modelo' to distinguish from other
-- capoeiristas with apelido "Índio" (e.g., Mestre Índio Maranhão,
-- Índio from Roque's era at Mercado Modelo 1940s-50s, etc.)
-- ============================================================

